cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE, cs.SD

The paper discusses a method to extract knowledge from a recurrent neural network (LSTM) that has learned to detect valid input sequences according to an unknown generative automaton. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves natural language processing (cs.CL) as it uses Reber's grammar variations as an example. Additionally, the paper deals with neural networks (cs.NE) and statistical learning (cs.SD).
